        "description": {
            "name": "description",
            "type": "java.lang.String",
            "value": "@version    $Id: Inflector.php 7078 2007-12-11 14:29:33Z matthew $\n\nZend_Filter_Inflector method 'filter' needs at least one param ($source).\nIf you define _only_ 'static' rules (without, for example, default ':' prefix) and set value to each one and you don't need to replace it with a $source array you should call 'filter' method without param.\n\nSure, as workaround you can call filter(null), filter(array()), ...\n\nActual code:\n{code}\npublic function filter($source)\n{\n    [...]\n}\n{code}\n\nProposed code:\n{code}\npublic function filter($source = null)\n{\n    [...]\n}\n{code}\n"
        },
